OL,3,CJersey's Education Minister says he
OL,4,Ccannot support introducing bilingual
OL,5,Cschools
OL,7,FJersey's Minister for Education says
OL,8,Fhe will not support the bilingual
OL,9,Fschool proposals which will be debated
OL,10,Fin the States Assembly on 22 October.
OL,12,FDeputy Rob Ward says introducing the
OL,13,Fschools is not a priority for the
OL,14,Fisland and would be too expensive.
OL,16,FIt comes after Deputy Sir Philip
OL,17,FBailhache wrote a proposition in
OL,18,FAugust to progressively phase in the
OL,19,Fintroduction of French-English
OL,20,Fbilingual lessons in three schools,
OL,21,Fbeginning with reception classes.
