OL,3,CJersey's Education Minister says he
OL,4,Ccannot support introducing bilingual
OL,5,Cschools
OL,7,FHowever, in an amendment to his
OL,8,Fproposition, Deputy Bailhache seeks to
OL,9,Fgain in-principle support for at least
OL,10,Ftwo English-French bilingual primary
OL,11,Fschools and requests the Minister for
OL,12,FEducation and Lifelong Learning to
OL,13,Fconduct a parental survey working with
OL,14,FStatistics Jersey.
OL,16,FIf the survey outcome is positive, the
OL,17,FMinister is then asked to appoint a
OL,18,Fproject manager to create at least two
OL,19,Fschools by September 2026.
