OL,3,CJersey's Education Minister says he
OL,4,Ccannot support introducing bilingual
OL,5,Cschools
OL,7,FHowever, in a report, Deputy Rob Ward
OL,8,Fsays he "understands Deputy
OL,9,FBailhache's passion and reasons for
OL,10,Fhis proposal, but unfortunately, when
OL,11,Fconsidered alongside the priorities,
OL,12,Fthe priority already given to French
OL,13,Flanguage tuition in primary and
OL,14,Fsecondary schools, and strong concerns
OL,15,Ffrom primary school Head Teachers, it
OL,16,Fcannot be supported at this time".
OL,18,F24 schools were sent a survey after
OL,19,Fthe lodged proposition, however, out
OL,20,Fof the 21 schools that responded, none
OL,21,Fvoted in favour of the idea.
