OL,3,CJersey's Education Minister says he
OL,4,Ccannot support introducing bilingual
OL,5,Cschools
OL,7,FDeputy Rob Ward also argues that
OL,8,FFrench is already taught in schools
OL,9,Fand has shown positive results, he
OL,10,Fstates that on average 75% of pupils
OL,11,Fachieve a secure grasp of French by
OL,12,Fthe end of Year 6 following the
OL,13,Fbespoke programme of study for French
OL,14,Fin Years 3, 4, 5 and 6, created and
OL,15,Fresourced by the French lead.
